{
  "stem": "1502.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the-- Hitler guaranteed that neutrality.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we knew-- we-- we believed that there is no danger-- what we are concerned.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Now, when Poland was invaded, the-- in Poland, persecutions started immediately.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we received-- since we were neutral, we were in a neutral country, we received lots of letters, which I still have, dozens of letters from the entire family in Poland-- from friends, from cousins, from anybody that knew our name, for help.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Each letter, each postcard was an SOS-- help; try to save us; do something; send us food-- I still have those letters.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There isn't much we could do at that time.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We did send packages of food to Poland, and we did answer the letters.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But I don't think that my father was in a position, or anybody else was in a position, to do anything for the people which were trapped in Poland.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the-- the letters were sent from-- from the ghetto in Warsaw, from the ghetto in Lodz.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And also, my uncle, my mother's brother, who was the [NON-ENGLISH] Rabbi at the time, he escaped to Vilna.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Vilna was Lithuania.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because as you know, when they invaded Poland, they-- they split Poland between Russia.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The Russians invaded Poland at the same time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That was the agreement between Ribbentrop and Molotov, that they split Poland.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Russians took a chunk.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The Germans took most of it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then they gave a little part to Lithuania.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So Vilna became Lithuania.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And my uncle escaped to Vilna, where they had a refuge for a while.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, Belgium, despite that they declared their neutrality, Hitler invaded Belgium on May the 10th, 1940.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I remember it was on a Friday.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And at 6 o'clock in the morning, I was awakened by-- by anti-aircraft artillery noise and bombing.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
